Mpumalanga Premier Refilwe Mtshweni-Tsipane JOHANNESBURG - Police minister Bheki Cele has asked police commissioner Khehla Sitole to investigate the Mpumalanga premier's failure to wear a mask in public. Refilwe Mtsweni-Tsipane was seen arriving at the cemetery for Jackson Mthembu's burial on Sunday without a mask. READ: There's enough room for mask convicts: Correctional Services She claims she was oblivious to the fact that her mask had broken. Earlier at the funeral service, deputy president David Mabuza signalled to Mtsweni-Tsipane to put her mask on as she left the podium. READ: Mpumalanga Premier apologises for 'missing mask' at Mthembu funeral Cele says necessary action must be taken against the premier should the police commissioner find she contravened COVID-19 regulations.